# Accessibility Standards (WCAG 2.1 AA)

## When to Use

- Building or editing React/Next.js UI components
- Reviewing frontend code for accessibility compliance
- Creating forms, modals, navigation, or interactive elements

## When NOT to Use

- Backend-only code, API routes, scripts, or CLI tools

## Core Rules

### 1. Semantic HTML First

Use native HTML elements before reaching for ARIA:

```tsx
// Bad: div with role
<div role="button" onClick={handleClick}>Submit</div>

// Good: native button
<button onClick={handleClick}>Submit</button>
```

Prefer `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<aside>`, `<header>`, `<footer>` over generic `<div>`.

### 2. Form Labels

Every input must have an associated label:

```tsx
// Bad: no label
<input type="email" placeholder="Email" />

// Good: explicit label
<label htmlFor="email">Email</label>
<input id="email" type="email" placeholder="user@example.com" />
```

### 3. Image Alt Text

All `<img>` elements must have `alt`. Decorative images use `alt=""`:

```tsx
// Informative
<img src="/logo.png" alt="Company logo" />

// Decorative
<img src="/divider.svg" alt="" role="presentation" />
```

### 4. Keyboard Navigation

- All interactive elements must be reachable via Tab
- Custom components need `tabIndex={0}` only if they are interactive and not natively focusable
- Never use `tabIndex` > 0
- Provide visible focus indicators (never `outline: none` without replacement)

```tsx
// Good: visible focus
<button className='focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:outline-none'>
  Save
</button>
```

### 5. ARIA When Needed

Use ARIA only when semantic HTML is insufficient:

```tsx
// Toggle button
<button aria-pressed={isActive} onClick={toggle}>
  Dark Mode
</button>

// Live region for dynamic content
<div aria-live="polite" role="status">
  {statusMessage}
</div>

// Modal
<dialog aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="dialog-title">
  <h2 id="dialog-title">Confirm Action</h2>
</dialog>
```

### 6. Color Contrast

- Normal text: minimum 4.5:1 contrast ratio
- Large text (18px+ or 14px+ bold): minimum 3:1
- UI components and icons: minimum 3:1

### 7. Headings

- One `<h1>` per page
- Heading levels must not skip (h1 -> h3 without h2)
- All headings must contain visible text or `aria-label`

### 8. Error Messages

Form errors must be programmatically associated:

```tsx
<label htmlFor="email">Email</label>
<input
  id="email"
  type="email"
  aria-invalid={!!error}
  aria-describedby={error ? "email-error" : undefined}
/>
{error && <p id="email-error" role="alert">{error}</p>}
```

### 9. Skip Navigation

Provide skip links for keyboard users:

```tsx
<a href='#main-content' className='sr-only focus:not-sr-only'>
  Skip to main content
</a>
```

### 10. Motion and Animation

Respect user preferences:

```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  *,
  *::before,
  *::after {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}
```

## Automated Testing

- Use `eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y` for static analysis
- Use `@axe-core/react` in development for runtime checks
- Use Playwright `browser_snapshot` (accessibility tree) for integration testing

## Checklist

- [ ] All images have appropriate `alt` text
- [ ] All form inputs have associated labels
- [ ] Color contrast meets WCAG AA minimums
- [ ] Keyboard navigation works for all interactive elements
- [ ] Focus indicators are visible
- [ ] Heading hierarchy is logical (no skipped levels)
- [ ] ARIA attributes are used correctly (no redundant roles)
- [ ] Error messages are programmatically linked to inputs
- [ ] Dynamic content uses `aria-live` regions
- [ ] Motion respects `prefers-reduced-motion`
